St. Nicholas Avenue, east side, south from W. 123rd Street (exxtreme right and not seen ). This thoroumhfare crosses Eighth venue and upon which apears the Ninth Avenue "El". The row of buildings beyond hame, form the east side of Eighth Avenue, from 121st Street to 122nd Street. At this point in earlier days, Bensons Lane branched eastward from the Harlem Road to Ninasbridge. The latter followed the preset line of St. Nicholas
Avenue.
